Founded in 2009, '''Against Equality (A.E.)''' is an online archive of writings and arts that critique mainstream gay and lesbian politics.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://goodmenproject.com/featured-content/working-against-equality-a-closer-look-at-queers-who-oppose-gay-marriage/ |title=Working Against Equality: A Closer Look at Queers Who Oppose Gay Marriage |publisher=Goodmenproject.com |date=2011-04-22 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> A.E. currently focuses on issues regarding the institution of [[marriage]],<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.salon.com/life/feature/2011/06/28/gay_marriage |title=Will marriage change gay love? |publisher=Salon.com |date=2011-06-28 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> the [[United States Armed Forces|U.S. military]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gayrva.com/2011/09/02/against-equality-on-dadt-repeal/ |title=Against Equality on DADT Repeal |publisher=Gayrva.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> and the [[prison-industrial complex]] via [[hate crime law]].
==Structure== Against Equality is an anti-capitalist collective of radical queer and trans writers, thinkers, and artists.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sgn.org/sgnnews39_13/page18.cfm |title='Equality' beyond marriage - An interview with activist Ryan Conrad |publisher=Sgn.org |date=2011-04-01 |accessdate=2014-06-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228033844/http://www.sgn.org/sgnnews39_13/page18.cfm |archivedate=2014-02-28 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultmontreal.com/2013/01/hate-crime-legislation-has-failed-us-against-equality/ |title=Hate Crime Legislation has Failed Us: Against Equality |publisher=Cultmontreal.com |date=2013-01-22 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> A.E. maintains an online [[archive]] of written work and cultural references. A.E. has also self-published three [[anthologies]] that highlight work from the three sections of their online archive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timeoutchicago.com/arts-culture/books/91564/gay-divorce |title=Gay Divorce |publisher=Timeoutchicago.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> These three anthologies were combined into a single book and was published by [[AK Press]] in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.akpress.org/againstequality-5365.html |title=Against Equality: Queer Revolution, Not Mere Inclusion from |publisher=AK Press |date=2014-03-20 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
==Publications== A.E. published its first book in the fall of 2010. ''Against Equality: Queer Critiques of Gay Marriage'' contains essays and op-ed pieces by prominent [[queer]] thinkers, including [[Kate Bornstein]], Eric A. Stanley, [[Dean Spade]], Craig Willse, [[Kenyon Farrow]], Kate Raphael, Deeg, [[John D'Emilio]], Ryan Conrad, [[Yasmin Nair]], MJ Kaufman, Katie Miles, and [[Mattilda Bernstein Sycamore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8801547-against-equality |title=Against Equality: Queer Critiques of Gay Marriage on |publisher=Goodreads.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> ''Against Equality: Queer Critiques of Gay Marriage'' ranked sixth on AK Press Distribution's Top 10 of 2010 list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.revolutionbythebook.akpress.org/top-10-of-2010-ak-press-distribution/ |title=Top 10 of 2010: AK Press Distribution |publisher=Revolutionbythebook.akpress.org |date=2011-01-19 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
A.E published the second book, ''Against Equality: Don’t Ask to Fight Their Wars'', in the fall of 2011 and contains a collection of essays and illustrations critiquing the mainstream gay and lesbian politics and its uncritical approach to [[Don't ask, don't tell]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.homotopiafilm.net/index.php/2011/07/21/books-books-and-more-books/|publisher=Homotopia Criminal Queers|title=Books, books and more books|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120723012245/http://www.homotopiafilm.net/index.php/2011/07/21/books-books-and-more-books/|date=21 July 2011|archivedate=23 July 2012}}</ref> Contributors include [[Mattilda Bernstein Sycamore]], Kenyon Farrow, Cecilia Cissell Lucas, Yasmin Nair, Erica Meiners, Therese Quinn, Tamara K. Nopper, Larry Goldsmith, Jamal Rashad Jones, [[Bill Andriette]], and illustrator Mr. Fish.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12151763-against-equality |title=Against Equality: Don't Ask to Fight Their Wars on |publisher=Goodreads.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
A.E. published the third and final book in its [[trilogy]], ''Against Equality: Prisons Will Not Protect You'', in the fall of 2012. This book focuses on [[hate crime law]] and the [[prison industrial complex]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Materville Studios - Host of Windy City Times |url=http://www.windycitymediagroup.com/lgbt/Against-Equality-launches-new-book-on-DADT-/37432.html |title=Against Equality launches new book on DADT |publisher=Windycitymediagroup.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> Contributors include [[Dean Spade]], Jason Lydon, the [[Sylvia Rivera Law Project]], Liliana Segura, Jack Aponte, Yasmin Nair, Imani Keith Henry, Sébastien Barraud, Erica Meiners, Liam Michaud, Josh Pavan, and Bridget Simpson.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15979911-against-equality |title=Against Equality: Prisons Will Not Protect You on |publisher=Goodreads.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
[[AK Press]] released a three-in-one anthology titled ''Against Equality: Queer Revolution, Not Mere Inclusion'' in March 2014 that combines the collective's previous three anthologies and includes a new introduction from the collective.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://akpressdistro.tumblr.com/post/77087609424/editor-q-a-with-ryan-conrad-of-against-equality |title=Editor Q&A with Ryan Conrad of Against Equality |publisher=Akpressdistro.tumblr.com |date=2014-02-18 |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
==Events== Members of the Against Equality collective have also traveled extensively to speak at bookstores, community spaces, colleges, and universities across the United States, Canada, Europe, Australia, and New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.againstequality.org/events/ |title=Events Listing |publisher=Against Equality |date= |accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref>
